Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 476
S.P. 216 In Senate, February 11, 2025
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on February 5, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator TEPLER of Sagadahoc.
Cosponsored by Representative DOUDERA of Camden and
Representatives: ANKELES of Brunswick, GRAMLICH of Old Orchard Beach.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 38 MRSA ยง1603, sub-ยง2-A is enacted to read:
3 2-A. Prohibition on loose polystyrene packing material. After January 1, 2027, a
4 person may not sell or offer to sell in this State any product composed in whole or in part
5 of loose polystyrene pieces used for packing material.
6 SUMMARY
77 This bill prohibits the sale of or offer for sale of loose polystyrene pieces used for
88 packing material, commonly called packing peanuts.
